  "modName": "Smelting Revamped Legendary",
  "summary": "This mod is mostly for the playing on the new Legendary difficult on Skyrim.  Add ranks to the Smiting kill tree, such as Steel smiting having 2 rank in it.  Purchasing both ranks for a certain thing(Steel, elven,etc..) Conidurably increase the improvement cappablilities and also allows for the smelting of armor, weapons, and misc items into ingots",
  "descriptionHtml": "WARNING: Might conflict with other mods that mess with the Smithing skill tree&#33; \r<br />This mod allows for you to take all those pesky weapons, armor, and junk that you no longer need and turn them into ingots at smelters to be used for something more useful. Also note options for things will only show up as long as you have at least 1 of the item in your inventory. \r<br />Example: The option to smelt Elven Armor will only appear if you have 1 in your inventory to begin with.\r<br />Optional files for the DLCs in the Downloads tab.\r<br />\r<br />More perks the the Smithing skill tree&#33;\r<br />Example. Rank 1: Steel Smithing- Can create Steel armor and weapons at forges, and improve them twice as much. \r<br />Rank 2: Steel Smithing- Can create Steel armor and weapons at forges, and improve them three times as much, as well as being able to breakthem down into ingots. \r<br />\r<br />When using the optional files for the DLCs make sure they are bellow the&#34;ErbosVanillaSmeltingRevampedLegendary&#34; File.\r<br />\r<br />If you think something need tweaking or you think there should be a item that I should add to this(Must be from the VANILLA Skyrim, no DLC....yet), let me know and I will see what I can do.\r<br />\r<br />Installation:\r<br />Nexus Mod Manager:\r<br />1-Click the &#34;DOWNLOAD(NMM)&#34; at the top of the screen or the downloads tab.\r<br />2-When installing a option mod from the downloads tab, you will be asked if you want to update, Select no to install the mod normally.\r<br />\r<br />Manual:\r<br />1- Download via the &#34;Download(Manual)&#34;\r<br />2- Drag the content of the &#34;Data&#34; folder into the Data folder of where you have the installation of Skyrim at  &#34;Skyrim/Data&#34;.\r<br />",
